<h3>Pawatta Leaves</h3>
<p>Pawatta leaves, also known as Justicia adhatoda or Malabar nut, are traditionally used as a medicinal herb in Sri Lanka and other parts of Asia, particularly for respiratory ailments like coughs, colds, and asthma, and also for skin conditions.<br><span style="color:red">Respiratory Issues:</span><br><span style="color:red">Cough and Cold Relief:</span>Pawatta leaves are known for their expectorant properties, helping to loosen mucus and ease breathing.<br><span style="color:red">Bronchitis and Asthma:</span> They are used to treat bronchitis and asthma, potentially due to their bronchodilator effects.<br>
<span style="color:red">Fever:</span>The plant is used to treat fever, including fever associated with malaria.</p>
